#Scatter Plot for Sepal Width
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
Iris_color_rep = {'Iris-Setosa':'orange', 'Iris-Versicolour':'green', 'Iris-Virginica':'red'}
for x in range(len(Iris_data_frame['sepal width (cm)'])):
    scatter_plot_Sepal_width = plt.scatter(Iris_data_frame['type'][x], Iris_data_frame['sepal width (cm)'][x], color=Iris_color_rep[Iris_data_frame['type'][x]])
scatter_plot_Sepal_width_title = plt.title('Sepal Width for all three types of Irises')
scatter_plot_Sepal_width_x_axis_title = plt.xlabel("Type")
scatter_plot_Sepal_width_y_axis_label = plt.ylabel("Sepal Width in cm")
plt.show()

#Implementing my KNN algorithm
def calculating_dist(i, j, dist, pt=2):
    if dist == "euclidean":
        return np.sqrt(np.sum((i-j)**2))
    elif dist == "manhattan":
        return np.sum(np.abs(i - j))
    elif dist == "minkowski":
        return np.sum(np.abs(i-j)**pt)**(1/pt)
class KNNalgorithm():
    def __init__(self, n=3, dist="euclidean"):
        self.n = n
        self.dist = dist
        
    def fit(self, Iris_X_train, Iris_Y_train):
        self.Iris_X_train = Iris_X_train
        self.Iris_Y_train = Iris_Y_train
        
    def predict(self, M):
        Predict_Y = np.zeros(M.shape[0])
        for q in range(M.shape[0]):
            Iris_dist = np.zeros(self.Iris_X_train.shape[0])
            for p in range(self.Iris_X_train.shape[0]):
                    Iris_dist[p] = calculating_dist(self.Iris_X_train[p,:], M[q,:], self.dist)
                    Iris_index = np.argsort(Iris_dist)
                    close_c = self.Iris_Y[Iris_index[:self.n]]
                    Iris_Count = Counter(close_c)
                    Predict_Y[q] = Iris_Count.most_common(1)[0][0]
        
        return Predict_Y
